235
00:16:01,840 --> 00:16:05,930
What if a student writer discovers
that he or she has too little to say?

236
00:16:06,940 --> 00:16:10,270
What or how can she or he deal with that?

237
00:16:12,780 --> 00:16:15,420
>> I think a student who has quote,

238
00:16:15,420 --> 00:16:22,260
too little to say, is usually a student
whose imagination is too narrow.

239
00:16:22,260 --> 00:16:26,440
Often, it's a student who has decided
to write about an abstract topic and

240
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:29,119
has just kept focusing on the abstraction.

241
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:36,020
When a student is, seems to be devoid of
ideas, when a writer is devoid of ideas,

242
00:16:36,020 --> 00:16:42,690
he or she should slow down and
brainstorm and brainstorm wildly.

243
00:16:45,750 --> 00:16:49,920
Go to a piece of paper and write down
everything you know about the topic, draw

244
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:56,980
diagrams on a piece of paper, draw idea
maps or mind maps, make lists of objects.

245
00:16:58,810 --> 00:17:00,450
Shift the focus, in other words.

246
00:17:00,450 --> 00:17:04,530
A student who doesn't have enough
to say has often gotten too

247
00:17:04,530 --> 00:17:07,500
tense in trying to say
something important.

248
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:10,320
It's a good idea to stop trying
to say something important and

249
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:13,430
