and replace them with shorter sentences.

275
00:18:36,930 --> 00:18:42,510
In terms of completeness,
a writer can do two things.

276
00:18:42,510 --> 00:18:45,080
It's asking himself a couple of questions.

277
00:18:45,080 --> 00:18:49,830
The first one is, what am I trying to say?

278
00:18:49,830 --> 00:18:51,720
Did I say it clearly?

279
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:54,990
And the second one is,
what must I not leave out?

280
00:18:57,100 --> 00:19:01,790
The very last question, which is,
what must I make sure not to leave out?

281
00:19:01,790 --> 00:19:03,280
It's very useful.

282
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:07,670
I use it myself all the time at the,
as I get to the end of a draft.

283
00:19:07,670 --> 00:19:10,712
I then ask myself, did I cover everything?

284
00:19:10,712 --> 00:19:15,370
And in particular, is there anything
I must make sure not to leave out?

285
00:19:15,370 --> 00:19:18,770
Often it turns out I have
left out something important.

286
00:19:18,770 --> 00:19:21,310
So, those are my final words on this.

287
00:19:21,310 --> 00:19:23,590
